{
  "texts": [
    "(2) Local Fine-tuning: Consider a federated learning system composed of 𝐾 clients, each holding a local fine-tuning dataset D 𝑘, where 𝑘 ∈ 1, 2,..., 𝐾.",
    "The adapted model 𝑾 𝒌 at client 𝑘 is:𝑾 𝒌 = W0 + 𝚫𝑾 𝒌 = W0 + 𝑩 𝒌 𝑨 𝒌(2)The fine-tuning objective is to minimize the local loss function L 𝑘 with respect to the adapter parameters 𝑩 𝒌 and 𝑨 𝒌:L 𝑘 W0 + 𝑩 𝒌 𝑨 𝒌; D 𝑘 = 1 𝑛 𝑘 𝑛 𝑘 ∑︁ 𝑖=1 ℓ 𝑓 W0 + 𝑩 𝒌 𝑨 𝒌; 𝒙 𝒌 𝒊, 𝒚 𝒌 𝒊(3)where (𝒙 𝒌 𝒊, 𝒚 𝒌 𝒊) ∈ D 𝑘 is one of the bug-fix code pairs in the fine-tuning dataset D 𝑘 and 𝑛 𝑘 is the size of D 𝑘. 𝑓 is the output function of the model and we employ a cross-entropy loss function ℓ to measure the difference between the probability distributions of the model output and actual code for each token in the sequences as follows:ℓ ( ŷ𝒌 𝒊, 𝒚 𝒌 𝒊; 𝒙 𝒌 𝒊) = - ∑︁ 𝑗 𝑄 ŷ𝑘 𝑖,𝑗 𝒙 𝒌 𝒊, ŷ𝑘 𝑖,1,..., ŷ𝑘 𝑖,𝑗 -1 × log 𝑃 𝑦 𝑘 𝑖,𝑗 𝒙 𝒌 𝒊, 𝑦 𝑘 𝑖,1,..., 𝑦 𝑘 𝑖,𝑗 -1 (4)where 𝑄 is the probability distribution for the predicted output ŷ𝒌 𝒊 and 𝑃 is the actual distribution for 𝒚 𝒌 𝒊. ŷ𝑘 𝑖,𝑗 ∈ ŷ𝒌 𝒊 and 𝑦 𝑘 𝑖,𝑗 ∈ 𝒚 𝒌 𝒊 are one of the tokens in the predicted output and actual code respectively.",
    "Then the optimized low-rank adapter parameters can be obtained by using various optimizers such as SGD:𝚫𝑾 * 𝒌 = 𝑩 * 𝒌 𝑨 * 𝒌 = 𝚫𝑾 𝒌 -𝜂ΔL 𝑘 W0 + 𝑩 𝒌 𝑨 𝒌; D 𝑘 (5)where 𝜂 is the learning rate.",
    "Note that in this framework the paged optimizers are utilized according to the setting of QLoRA, which are able to automatically transfer the information from GPU to CPU for error-free GPU processing when GPU encounters out-of-memory issues [17].",
    "(3) Fine-tuned Model Upload: Instead of uploading the entire fine-tuned LLMs, clients upload only the fine-tuned adapters 𝑩 * 𝒌 𝑨 * 𝒌 to the central server."
  ]
}